<subSubSection id="A2D3C1A9FF9D3849FF75D5C2FD3EABD7" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="429" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF9D3849FF75D5C2FD3EABD7" blockId="7.[151,1436,1999,2024]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,536]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="429" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF9D3846FF75D5C2FE86ACEA" bold="true" box="[151,273,1999,2024]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Compound eyes dichoptic, upper division small, about 
<number id="5C018005FF9D3846FC62D5DDFC1DACEA" box="[896,906,2000,2024]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="5C018005FF9D3846FC76D5DDFC25ACEA" box="[916,946,2000,2024]" pageId="7" pageNumber="428" value="10.0">10</number>
as large as lower division. Posterior margin of epandrium concaved medially, W-shaped, lateral margin slightly concaved medially; cercus bilobate, each lobe conical, round apically, with several long hairs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A2D3C1A9FF923848FF25D2D2FE0DADAD" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="430" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" type="description">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF923849FF25D2D2FC07A91A" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF923849FF25D2D2FE3EABFA" bold="true" box="[199,425,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body length 4.0– 
<quantity id="2D313FC7FF923849FD67D2D2FD75ABF5" box="[645,738,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<number id="5C018005FF923849FC6FD2D2FC38ABFA" box="[909,943,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="5.5">5.5</number>
–6.0 mm, wing width 
<quantity id="2D313FC7FF923849FB22D2EDFAC7ABF5" box="[1216,1360,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" unit="mm" value="1.7999999999999998" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.7">1.7–1.9 mm</quantity>
. Head uniformly dark brown. Ocellar triangle brown. Head mostly without hairs, except eyes with two long hairs along dorsal margin. Compound eyes dichoptic, boundary of upper division and lower division conspicuous; upper division about 
<number id="5C018005FF923849FEA7D341FED8AA66" box="[325,335,332,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="5C018005FF923849FEBBD341FEE0AA66" box="[345,375,332,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="10.0">10</number>
as large as lower division, dark brown with pubescences; lower division dark brown with pubescences. Ocelli brick-red, prominent. Antenna longer than head width, scape and pedicel short, with several long hairs medially; first flagellomere slightly constricted basally, other flagellomeres cylindrical; antenna uniformly dark brown with short hairs. Proboscis dark brown with brown hairs. Palpus five-segmented, first segment short, segments 
<number id="5C018005FF923849FE5BD3D1FE74AAF6" box="[441,483,476,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
long, fifth segment slender and long, as long as the total length of segments 
<number id="5C018005FF923849FA88D3D1FA00AAF6" box="[1386,1431,476,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
; palpus mostly yellow, 
<number id="5C018005FF923849FE71D3F2FE37A91A" box="[403,416,511,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" value="5.0">5</number>
th segment yellow brown, with brown hairs.
</paragraph>
<caption id="BEB6C2AAFF923849FF75D5A9FAE0ACB9" box="[151,1399,1956,1979]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226451/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" targetBox="[316,1277,599,1928]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF923849FF75D5A9FAE0ACB9" blockId="8.[151,1399,1956,1979]" box="[151,1399,1956,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF923849FF75D5A9FEC4ACB8" bold="true" box="[151,339,1956,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">FIGURES 16–17.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2DC9E9A1FF923849FEB8D5A8FDD8ACB9" box="[346,591,1957,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Blepharicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hebeiensis" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF923849FEB8D5A8FDD8ACB9" box="[346,591,1957,1979]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">Blepharicera hebeiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C38EF34BFF923849FDB7D5ABFD37ACB9" box="[597,672,1958,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429" rank="species">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF923849FDB7D5ABFD37ACB9" bold="true" box="[597,672,1958,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="429">sp.nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 16: Habitus of male, lateral view; 17: Wing. Scale bar: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="BEB6C2AAFF933848FF75D6A5FD26AFDC" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226452/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" targetBox="[155,1426,186,1166]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF933848FF75D6A5FD26AFDC" blockId="9.[151,1436,1192,1246]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF933848FF75D6A5FECDAFBC" bold="true" box="[151,346,1192,1215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">FIGURES 18–20.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2DC9E9A1FF933848FE84D6A4FDF5AFBD" box="[358,610,1193,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Blepharicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hebeiensis" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF933848FE84D6A4FDF5AFBD" box="[358,610,1193,1215]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
Blepharicera 
<taxonomicName id="2DC9E9A1FF933848FE1AD6A4FDF5AFBD" box="[504,610,1193,1215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" rank="species" species="hebeiensis" status="sp.nov.">hebeiensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C38EF34BFF933848FD8CD6A4FD2DAFBC" box="[622,698,1193,1214]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" rank="species">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF933848FD8CD6A4FD2DAFBC" bold="true" box="[622,698,1193,1214]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">sp.nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 18: Genitalia, dorsal view; 19: Genitalia, ventral view; 20: Gonostylus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 18–20 = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="EA769222FF933848FF25D707FF42AEB1" blockId="9.[151,1437,1290,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
Thoracic dorsum uniformly brown; pleuron mostly brown with yellow plaque; only scutellum with dense patches of hairs on anterior margin. Legs mostly yellow brown except coxae and trochanters yellow; legs with uniformly black hairs, tibiae without spurs. Wing (
<figureCitation id="72F28EA7FF933848FD2DD75FFCB6AE69" box="[719,801,1362,1387]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 17" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1956,1979]" captionTargetBox="[316,1277,599,1928]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[300,1288,589,1936]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 17. Blepharicera hebeiensis sp. nov. (male). 16: Habitus of male, lateral view; 17: Wing. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226451/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
Fig. 
<number id="5C018005FF933848FCE6D75EFCB6AE69" box="[772,801,1363,1387]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) subhyaline, veins brown. Sc rudimentary, not ending at base of Rs; Rs straight, a little longer than r-m; r-m straight. Base of halter yellow, knob brown with short brown hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA769222FF933848FF25D7B3FCADAD89" blockId="9.[151,1437,1290,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
Abdominal tergites mostly brown, tergites 
<number id="5C018005FF933848FD20D7B3FD7BAED5" box="[706,748,1470,1495]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
with narrow yellow brown band basally; sternites mostly yellow brown; hairs on abdomen dark brown. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="72F28EA7FF933848FC65D7EFFB80AEF9" box="[903,1047,1506,1531]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 20" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1192,1215]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,186,1166]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,179,1172]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 20. Blepharicera hebeiensis sp. nov. (male). 18: Genitalia, dorsal view; 19: Genitalia, ventral view; 20: Gonostylus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 18 – 20 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226452/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
Figs. 
<number id="5C018005FF933848FC2ED7EEFB80AEF9" box="[972,1047,1507,1531]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="19.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="18.0">18–20</number>
</figureCitation>
): Posterior margin of epandrium concaved medially, W-shaped, lateral margin slightly concaved medially, with several long hairs; hypandrium slightly narrow basally, posteromedial margin concave; cercus bilobate, each lobe conical, round apically, with several long hairs; outer gonostylus swollen and slightly notched apically in lateral view, with uniformly hairs; inner gonocoxal lobe transparent, slender; paramere slender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA769222FF933848FF25D49BFE0DADAD" blockId="9.[151,1437,1290,2035]" box="[199,410,1686,1711]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF933848FF25D49BFE89ADAD" bold="true" box="[199,286,1686,1711]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
