<subSubSection id="A2D3C1A9FF933848FF25D547FBADACF1" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EA769222FF933848FF25D547FBADACF1" blockId="9.[151,1437,1290,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF933848FF25D547FEACAC61" bold="true" box="[199,315,1866,1891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2DC9E9A1FF933848FCE8D546FC0DAC61" box="[778,922,1867,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Blepharicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yamasakii">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF933848FCE8D546FC0DAC61" box="[778,922,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">B. yamasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily separated from the latter by the following features: the apical flagellomere is equal in length to the penultimate flagellomere; epandrium transverse, posterior margin concave medially, V-shaped; cercus bilobate, each lobe conical, round apically. In 
<taxonomicName id="2DC9E9A1FF933848FA66D59EFE9EACCC" class="Insecta" family="Blephariceridae" genus="Blepharicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yamasakii">
<emphasis id="D8BD4E30FF933848FA66D59EFE9EACCC" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="430">B. yamasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the apical flagellomere is 
<number id="5C018005FF933848FDDFD5BBFDF7ACCD" box="[573,608,1974,1999]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times the length of the penultimate, the epandrium is transverse with the posterior margin truncate, each lobe of the cercus is semicircular (
<bibRefCitation id="8E58EFD3FF933848FC98D5D7FBBAACF1" author="Kitakami" box="[890,1069,2010,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" refString="Kitakami, S. (1950) The revision of the Blephariceridae of Japan and adjacent territories. The Journal of Kumamoto Women's University, 2, 15 - 90." type="journal article" year="1950">
Kitakami, 
<number id="5C018005FF933848FC13D5D7FBBAACF1" box="[1009,1069,2010,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="430" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
